rca of the issue:
BUG: Trial counter stuck at 14d 00h 00m 00s. RCA: /app/frontend/src/react-app/components/TrialGate.tsx line 22-23 reads `data.startedAt` (numeric epoch ms) from localStorage.fuelpro_trial. However the actual persisted shape (written elsewhere — likely AuthLogin/session manager) is `{userId, email, deviceFingerprint, trialStartedAt: <ISO string>, trialUsed, verified, ipHash}`. Field name mismatch → `data.startedAt === undefined` → line 23 fallback `let startedAt = data.startedAt || Date.now();` → startedAt is reset to current time on every getTrialState() call → msLeft = TRIAL_MS - (Date.now()-Date.now()) = TRIAL_MS exactly, every second. Reproduction: register fresh user → login → observe banner shows '14d 00h 00m 00s left' and never changes. Mitigation:
```
const startedAt = Number.isFinite(data.startedAt)
    ? data.startedAt
    : (data.trialStartedAt ? Date.parse(data.trialStartedAt) : Date.now());
if (!Number.isFinite(startedAt) || startedAt > Date.now()) { ... }
```
Additionally normalize the writer so both forms exist (write both `startedAt: ms` and `trialStartedAt: ISO`) for backwards-compat with any legacy code.
